comments.body:
Whew! CI is now green. The re-pushes were expected and necessary (well, most of them. Two were unnecessary CI churn due to my carelessness).

I have updated the commit message and PR description to reflect everything I did; please review that carefully. (Commit message is much much longer than the actual test diffs). (Oh, and my PR description formatting is horrible, so I really do recommend reading the git commit message instead).

@nalind I'd appreciate your attention on each of the four image changes I made in individual tests, to make sure there aren't any subtle image properties that will be lost by moving between repos.

@vrothberg I didn't understand your comment from this morning, and I choose to leave `registries.conf` exactly as it was on my first submission yesterday. It is exactly the same as the one used in podman CI, and (more importantly) it works this way. 

Thanks all for your help and feedback.
